SIMPLE: fossick
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fossick
<hw>Fos"sick</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Dial. E.
<ets>fossick</ets>, <ets>fossuck</ets>, a troublesome person,
<ets>fussick</ets> to potter over one's work, <ets>fussock</ets> to
bustle about; of uncertain origin. Cf. <er>Fuss</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>To search for gold by picking at stone or earth
or among roots in isolated spots, picking over abandoned workings, etc.;
hence, to steal gold or auriferous matter from another's claim.</def>
<mark>[Australia]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To search about; to rummage.</def></p>

<p><q>A man who has <qex>fossicked</qex> in nature's byways.</q>
<rj><qau>D. Macdonald.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fossil</ent>⟦br⟧
